interfaces.label: GetSearchBarFilterOptions
description: Options for the {@link SavedObjectsTaggingApiUi.getSearchBarFilter | getSearchBarFilter api}

children.label: useName
description:
If set to true, will use the tag's `name` instead of `id` for the tag field clause, which is recommended
for a better end-user experience.

Defaults to true.

children.label: tagField
description: The tag clause field name to generate the query. Defaults to `tag`.

children.label: getState
description: Return the current state of the cache

children.label: getState$
description: Return an observable that will emit everytime the cache's state mutates.

interfaces.label: ParseSearchQueryOptions
description: Options for the {@link SavedObjectsTaggingApiUi.parseSearchQuery | parseSearchQuery api}

children.label: useName
description:
If set to true, will assume the tag clause is using tag names instead of ids.
In that case, will perform a reverse lookup from the client-side tag cache to resolve tag ids from names.

Defaults to true.

children.label: tagField
description: The tag clause field name to extract the tags from. Defaults to `tag`.

interfaces.label: SavedObjectSaveModalTagSelectorComponentProps
description: Props type for the {@link SavedObjectsTaggingApiUiComponent.SavedObjectSaveModalTagSelector | SavedObjectSaveModalTagSelector component}

children.label: initialSelection
description:
Ids of the initially selected tags.
Changing the value of this prop after initial mount will not rerender the component (see component description for more details)

children.label: onTagsSelected
description: tags selection callback

children.label: client
description: The client to perform tag-related operations on the server-side

children.label: cache
description:
A client-side auto-refreshing cache of the existing tags. Can be used
to synchronously access the list of tags.

children.label: ui
description: UI API to use to add tagging capabilities to an application

interfaces.label: SavedObjectsTaggingApiUi
description: React components and utility methods to use the SO tagging feature

children.label: getTag
description: Return a Tag from an ID

children.label: hasTagDecoration
description: Type-guard to safely manipulate tag-enhanced `SavedObject` from the `savedObject` plugin.

children.label: getSearchBarFilter
description: Return a filter that can be used to filter by tag with `EuiSearchBar` or EUI tables using `EuiSearchBar`.

children.label: getTableColumnDefinition
description:
Return the column definition to be used to display the tags in a EUI table.
The table's items must be of the `SavedObject` type (or at least have their references available
via the `references` field)

children.label: convertNameToReference
parseSearchQuery
description:
Parse given query using EUI's `Query` syntax, and return the search term and the tag references
to be used when using the `_find` API to retrieve the filtered objects.

children.label: query
description: The query to parse

children.label: options
description: see {@link ParseSearchQueryOptions}

children.label: getTagIdsFromReferences
description: Returns the object ids for the tag references from given references array

children.label: getTagIdFromName
description:
Returns the id for given tag name. Will return `undefined`
if the given name does not match any existing tag.

children.label: updateTagsReferences
description:
Returns a new references array that replace the old tag references with references to the
new given tag ids, while preserving all non-tag references.

description: {@link SavedObjectsTaggingApiUiComponent | React components} to support the tagging feature.

Component to be used with the `options` property of the `SavedObjectSaveModal` or `SavedObjectSaveModalOrigin`
modals from the `savedObjects` plugin. It displays the whole field row and handles the 'stateless' nature
of props passed to inline components

signature: SavedObject & { getTags(): string[]; setTags(tags: string[]): void; }

children.label: registerTaggingApi
description:
Register a provider for the tagging API.

Only one provider can be registered, subsequent calls to this method will fail.

children.label: isTaggingAvailable
description: Returns true if the tagging feature is available (if a provider registered the API)

children.label: getTaggingApi
description:
Returns the tagging API, if registered.
This will always returns a value if `isTaggingAvailable` returns true, and undefined otherwise.
